title: Catching an Explosion in Water at 5 Million FPS - The Slow Mo Guys

media:group.media:title: Catching an Explosion in Water at 5 Million FPS - The Slow Mo Guys
media:group.media:description:
#PrimeVideoCreator Shaped charges are capable of smashing through a target at a speed of 10 Kilometres per second. Gav and Dan whip out the serious kit for this one. AD- Watch The Terminal List now on Prime Video: https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09HZ4BV5X
5 million frames per second played back at 25fps is the equivalent of slowing down 1 second of real time to over 2 days of playback.
Big thanks to the Colorado School of Mines for letting us back and for the use of their explosives and Shimadzu camera.
